  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Salesforce/CloudSense Lead",
  "description": "<p>We are partnering with a leading telecom client to hire a Salesforce / CloudSense Lead to drive large-scale digital transformation across CRM and Order Management platforms. You will lead the design and delivery of Salesforce and CloudSense solutions, ensuring high-quality, scalable systems that support complex enterprise sales and order journeys.<br /></p><p>Responsibilities:</p><ul><li>Lead end-to-end solution delivery across the SDLC – from requirements to production.Own technical design and delivery for Salesforce and CloudSense implementations.</li><li>Drive product modelling, pricing, and order orchestration using CloudSense CPQ.</li><li>Define and enforce DevOps standards including CI/CD, automation, and testing.Partner with business, IT, and vendors to deliver enterprise-grade CRM and OM solutions.</li><li>Ensure system stability, performance, security, and continuous improvement.</li><li>Troubleshoot issues across sandbox, staging, and production environments.</li><li>Mentor engineers and provide strong technical leadership.</li></ul><p>Requirements:</p><ul><li>8+ years of experience in Salesforce architecture, development, and integration.</li><li>Strong expertise in CloudSense CPQ (product modelling, pricing, orchestration).</li><li>Hands-on with Sales Cloud, Service Cloud, Community Cloud, Apex, LWC, Visualforce.</li><li>Experience with DevOps on Salesforce (CI/CD, version control, automation).</li><li>Strong knowledge of APIs, integrations, and microservices.</li><li>Excellent stakeholder communication and leadership skills.</li><li>Salesforce and/or CloudSense certifications are a strong advantage.</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 8,
